availableBadges.label: Data Sources Disclosed
availableBadges.description: This chart depicts a compilation of the latest 2100 median warming projections from UNEP, CAT, IEA, and Climate Resource (as of 9 Nov 2021), compared with IPCC AR6 WG1 SSP scenario values
availableBadges.tooltipContent: This chart depicts a compilation of the latest 2100 median warming projections from UNEP, CAT, IEA, and Climate Resource (as of 9 Nov 2021), compared with IPCC AR6 WG1 SSP scenario values

availableBadges.label: Contains Predictions
availableBadges.description: Every bar shows model-based, scenario-dependent future warming estimates rather than observations, signalling that numbers rely on underlying assumptions and may evolve as models or pledges change.
availableBadges.tooltipContent: Every bar shows model-based, scenario-dependent future warming estimates rather than observations, signalling that numbers rely on underlying assumptions and may evolve as models or pledges change.

availableBadges.label: Actual Time Offset
availableBadges.description: Compiled on 9 November 2021 from UNEP, CAT, IEA & CR.
availableBadges.tooltipContent: Compiled on 9 November 2021 from UNEP, CAT, IEA & CR.

availableBadges.label: Multiple Data Sources
availableBadges.description: Estimates compiled from multiple independent groups (UNEP, CAT, IEA, CR).
availableBadges.tooltipContent: Estimates compiled from multiple independent groups (UNEP, CAT, IEA, CR).

availableBadges.label: Uncertainty Shown
availableBadges.description: Each bar reports the median (50th-percentile) warming plus a central range printed inside the column. The span reflects variation across integrated-assessment and climate models; wider ranges indicate lower agreement.
availableBadges.tooltipContent: Each bar reports the median (50th-percentile) warming plus a central range printed inside the column. The span reflects variation across integrated-assessment and climate models; wider ranges indicate lower agreement.

availableBadges.label: Definition: CO emissions
availableBadges.description: CO released from burning fossil fuels (coal, oil, gas) and from certain industrial processes. Includes emissions from transport, electricity generation, heating, and industry, plus gas flaring. Also includes process CO from cement and steel production.
availableBadges.tooltipContent: CO released from burning fossil fuels (coal, oil, gas) and from certain industrial processes. Includes emissions from transport, electricity generation, heating, and industry, plus gas flaring. Also includes process CO from cement and steel production.

availableBadges.label: Missing Data
availableBadges.description: These figures dont include CO emissions from land-use change (e.g., deforestation or reforestation).
availableBadges.tooltipContent: These figures dont include CO emissions from land-use change (e.g., deforestation or reforestation).
